<subSubSection id="1DDBF8062B9909BE07BE745159AB6ACA" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="3DF2A9E19EF3EAA6E5479ADBD816CCB7" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6F66C65AE43D63E722DBA8BAD4D37681" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">
Most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="E53694572DA9E5E082C385198B8880E6" authorityName="Wedd" authorityYear="1854" baseAuthorityName="Buch. - Ham. ex D. Don" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Urticaceae" genus="Pilea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Urticales" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="scripta">
<emphasis id="DB4F2172790F25AF441766EBBB9CE881" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">Pilea scripta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from which it can be distinguished by the shorter stems, ovate rather than elliptic or oblong leaves, stipules with auriculate bases rather than deltate ones, the staminate tepals not ribbed and the sub-compressed elliptic rather than ovoid achenes with smooth non verrucose surfaces.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="24E6A37E999FB97FC32FC91F272DE4B4" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" type="type">
<paragraph id="E5B0FD566DAF9653808024C829629585" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">Type.</paragraph>
