<paragraph id="3E1CFDC342DEEB4C8175E469001EC514" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5F00B745FD904830870B7BA8122EADAA" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="55" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
Comparison of the holotype and paratype material with type specimens from the herbaria listed in the methods section recovered 
<taxonomicName id="985710F32D1E4D4622C93F732DA8BE7D" authorityName="Wedd" authorityYear="1854" baseAuthorityName="Buch. - Ham. ex D. Don" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Urticaceae" genus="Pilea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Urticales" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="scripta">
<emphasis id="AD529BC6C82F4A13C933E23F21A40CD9" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Pilea scripta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Buch.-Ham. ex D.Don) Wedd. and 
<taxonomicName id="5DFA302AC8D4C617C10BBFBE9C01A61A" authorityName="Hand - Mazz" authorityYear="1929" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Urticaceae" genus="Pilea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Urticales" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis id="C9A404BA607272551CF615F56C30B168" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Pilea gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Handel-Mazzetti as most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="0A56946D03CF49486217043DB9AFB29E" authorityName="A. K. Monro, C. J. Chen &amp; Y. G. Wei" authorityYear="2012" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Urticaceae" genus="Pilea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Urticales" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="cavernicola">
<emphasis id="8A66268AADB03B895AF5D2AEEB3E5092" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Pilea cavernicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="19A001867A1CE6BCD1AD9F9C309C067C" authorityName="Wedd" authorityYear="1854" baseAuthorityName="Buch. - Ham. ex D. Don" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Urticaceae" genus="Pilea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Urticales" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="scripta">
<emphasis id="D7A101CFAF889DCDE6A0C5F58026F972" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Pilea scripta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="A10D86FE03ADFFDCB5C1524E4C5478A4" authorityName="A. K. Monro, C. J. Chen &amp; Y. G. Wei" authorityYear="2012" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Urticaceae" genus="Pilea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Urticales" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="cavernicola">
<emphasis id="ECE1F78E65EF18E7FED13F3774EE10AA" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Pilea cavernicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on stem height, leaf shape, stipule shape, staminate tepal morphology and achene morphology as summarised in 
<tableCitation id="4F0C47ADE8951D1853507F27AA03FFB1" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. XX" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/4F219DFE92B8E01AB358DEA3381DE57C" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" tableUuid="4F219DFE92B8E01AB358DEA3381DE57C">Table 1</tableCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName id="1E33551D63F492C5328FF420DFD19C40" authorityName="Hand - Mazz" authorityYear="1929" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Urticaceae" genus="Pilea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Urticales" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis id="35839AD06C71083800F83FCCE1870E3D" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Pilea gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="CC7684B5ACF8DDF7E8B18872DD4474C4" authorityName="A. K. Monro, C. J. Chen &amp; Y. G. Wei" authorityYear="2012" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Urticaceae" genus="Pilea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Urticales" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="cavernicola">
<emphasis id="2AD57C44A291EB7641EF3B5169FA9AF9" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Pilea cavernicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on leaf shape, stipule morphology, staminate and pistillate inflorescence morphology and achene morphology as summarised in 
<tableCitation id="5480540F2BCD159F883DF10335D654F3" captionStart="Table 2" captionStartId="T2" captionText="Table 2. XX" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/2A8649446BCC48B21B9E508E3921F40F" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="55" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" tableUuid="2A8649446BCC48B21B9E508E3921F40F">
Table 
<pageBreakToken id="82DCCBC05C53FAA528D167AD742C6EF3" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" start="start">2</pageBreakToken>
</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B0EBC694F3055AB2D841F091D35D692D" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">
Pilea cavernicola falls within 
<bibRefCitation id="BD3B4347A2758EE29991DFD3A4826568" author="Weddell, HA" journalOrPublisher="American Journal of Botany" pageId="7" pageNumber="58" refId="B9" refString="Weddell, HA, 1869. Pilea. In: deCandolle ALLP (Ed) Prodromus 16(1), Treuttel and Wurtz, Paris, 104-163." title="Pilea. In: deCandolle ALLP (Ed) Prodromus 16 (1), Treuttel and Wurtz, Paris, 104 - 163." year="1869">
<normalizedToken id="9C624D0866AAC082A7E09423164FA79C" originalValue="Weddell’s">Weddell's</normalizedToken>
(1869)
</bibRefCitation>
Dentatae-Gerontogeae subdivision and 
<bibRefCitation id="A832ED67BEDB3A9B66AEDE4A0E05DD97" author="Chen, CJ" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Botanical Research Harbin" pageId="7" pageNumber="58" pagination="1 - 132" refId="B1" refString="Chen, CJ, 1982. A monograph of Pilea (Urticaceae) in China. Bulletin of Botanical Research Harbin 2 (3): 1 - 132" title="A monograph of Pilea (Urticaceae) in China." volume="2" year="1982">
<normalizedToken id="224D4A56015F9DCFD49BEAF15B661B00" originalValue="Chen’s">Chen's</normalizedToken>
(1982)
</bibRefCitation>
Urticella Section of the genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E61F550445260FCDDDE6438B5F94B15C" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="C766ED01E2863E7014DF4FA325F64DB1" bold="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">Conservation status.</emphasis>
Using IUCN criteria (
<bibRefCitation id="FBB2571077C05664B332F241AC14CD70" author="International Union for Conservation of Nature and Natural Resources Species Survival Commission," journalOrPublisher="International Union for Conservation of Nature and Natural Resources, Gland and Cambridge" pageId="7" pageNumber="58" refId="B4" refString="International Union for Conservation of Nature and Natural Resources Species Survival Commission, , 2001. IUCN Red List Categories: Version 3.1. International Union for Conservation of Nature and Natural Resources, Gland and Cambridge, 70 pp." title="IUCN Red List Categories: Version 3.1." year="2001">IUCN 2001</bibRefCitation>
) 
<taxonomicName id="86B3AB457F164122FD98EB3A2C0A7E88" authorityName="A. K. Monro, C. J. Chen &amp; Y. G. Wei" authorityYear="2012" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Urticaceae" genus="Pilea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Urticales" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="cavernicola">
<emphasis id="21659BA1F9BA6C09E6ED182E20E44EBF" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">Pilea cavernicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is considered Vulnerable (VU). 
<taxonomicName id="6C60B75051F73F73DB9B909E45AF2FC1" authorityName="A. K. Monro, C. J. Chen &amp; Y. G. Wei" authorityYear="2012" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Urticaceae" genus="Pilea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Urticales" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="cavernicola">
<emphasis id="BE24EE6AC0C50CEC6C890C11555E888F" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">Pilea cavernicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from only two localities (IUCN criteria D2, number of locations &lt;5). At these localities the populations of this species comprises ca 100-200 mature individuals (IUCN criteria D1, number of mature individuals &lt;1000). Using the IUCN methodology our Global Conservation Assessment for 
<taxonomicName id="64774A7BA759E4011A007F7670216E72" authorityName="A. K. Monro, C. J. Chen &amp; Y. G. Wei" authorityYear="2012" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Urticaceae" genus="Pilea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Urticales" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="cavernicola">
<emphasis id="C18721B159BF458C559C7CE3916FCFD8" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">Pilea cavernicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is Vulnerable (VU)based on criteria D1 and D2: population size and number of locations combined with a plausible future threat that could drive this taxon to Endangered in a very short time. Plausible threats include the location of both caves at the edge of agricultural land, the use of the entrance of one of the cave localities (Yangzi cave) to cultivate medicinal plants (
<taxonomicName id="1C2946262329DACBA0EDA19D650AB34B" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Papaveraceae" genus="Corydalis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Papaverales" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="32BED1818FEC39DAABAAF6077DAFCF27" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">Corydalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp.), requiring the terracing and tilling of the substrate. In addition mining is growing rapidly in the whole region and any localities close to roads are vulnerable to exploitation.
</paragraph>
